By Train:
Rehman (Economy) Rs.32,000/ head
TezGam (AC Standard) at Rs.37,000/ head
TezGam (AC Business Class): Rs.39,000/ head
Green Line (AC Business Class): Rs.42,000/ head

----------------------------------
(For Couples or 2 persons sharing a separate room)
Rs. 3,000/- per head extra or Rs.6000/couple
----------------------------------

Under 3 years Children - Free of Charge (Lap or on folding seat if available) Only 1 child will be free
3-8 years Children - Half Charges (folding seat)
8 plus years Children - Full Charges

📱 Contact For Booking
0333-3261622 (Zaheer Hussain)

ITINERARY

🚐 Departure from Karachi Cantt Railway Station
For Islamabad
Rehman at 10 AM
TezGam at 5:30 PM
Green Line at 10 PM

🗓 DAY 2 (14 June - Friday)
Arrival in Islamabad:
Rehman at 08:30 AM
TezGam at 7:00 PM
Green Line at 8:00 PM

Hotel Check in for participants.

🗓 DAY 3 (15 June - Saturday)
👫 Departure from Islamabad (Faizabad/ Daewoo) at 4:00 AM
🚌 Sightseeing on the way (Abbotabad, Mansehra, Balakot)
🍴 Short stay at Abbotabad or Balakot for Breakfast
🛏 Short stay in Naran
🚌 Visit Lulusar Lake and short stop there
📷 Photo session at Babusar Top
🍕 Dinner in Chilas
🏨 Overnight stay in Chilas

🗓 DAY 4 (16 June - Sunday)
🍴 Breakfast in Chilas
🚐 Departure for Skardu and on the way brief stop at (View of mighty Nanga Parbat at Thalichi, meeting point of 3 greatest mountain ranges and Confluence of River Indus & River Gilgit)
🛏 Reach Skardu
🍕 Dinner in Skardu
🏨 Night stay in Skardu

🗓 DAY 5 (17 June - Monday)
🍴 Breakfast in Skardu
🚐 Departure for Deosai Plains on jeeps
🌊 Visit Satpara Lake
🌊 Short stays at Kala pani, Bara Pani etc
🌊 Visit Sheosar Lake
🚌 Back to Skardu
🍔 Dinner and Night stay in Skardu Hotel

🗓 DAY 6 (18 June - Tuesday)
🍴 Breakfast in Skardu

🚌 Visit Shigar fort
🚌 Back to Skardu
🍔 Dinner in Skardu
🏨 Overnight Stay at Skardu Hotel

🗓 DAY 7 (19 June - Wednesday)

🍴 Breakfast in Skardu
🚐 Departure from Skardu

🏨 Night stay in Hotel

🗓 DAY 8 (20 June - Thursday)

🗓 DAY 9 (21 June - Friday)

Skardu  is a city in Gilgit-Baltistan region of Pakistan, and serves as the capital of Skardu District. Skardu is located in the 10 kilometres (6 miles) wide by 40 kilometres (25 miles) long Skardu Valley, at the confluence of the Indus and Shigar Rivers at an elevation of nearly 2,500 metres (8,202 feet). The city is an important gateway to the eight-thousanders of the nearby Karakoram Mountain range. The town is located on the Indus river, which separates the Karakoram Range from the Himalayas.
